OL,3,CBusiness rates 'double hit' to cost
OL,4,CEnglish firms #2.5 billion next year
OL,6,FRevaluations of the tax are revenue
OL,7,Fneutral across the country, meaning
OL,8,Fthat the overall tax take should not
OL,9,Fchange, but that the size of bills
OL,10,Fwill be distributed based on changing
OL,11,Fvaluations in certain sectors and
OL,12,Fregions.
OL,14,FHowever, despite this revaluation,
OL,15,Fbusiness rates yields will still rise
OL,16,Fin line with inflation from April.
OL,18,FThe increase in business rates is
OL,19,Ftypically based on the consumer price
OL,20,Findex (CPI) inflation measure for
OL,21,FSeptember.
