OL,3,CBusiness rates 'double hit' to cost
OL,4,CEnglish firms #2.5 billion next year
OL,6,FTherefore, this year's September
OL,7,Freading will dictate how large an
OL,8,Fincrease firms have next year.
OL,10,FThe Bank of England said earlier this
OL,11,Fmonth that climbing food prices were
OL,12,Fpushing inflation higher and predicted
OL,13,Fthat inflation would rise to 4% in
OL,14,FSeptember, above previous projections.
OL,16,FThis would add #1.11 billion to the
OL,17,Fbusiness rates burden in England,
OL,18,Faccording to analysis by Ryan.
