OL,3,CBusiness rates 'double hit' to cost
OL,4,CEnglish firms #2.5 billion next year
OL,6,FHowever, experts said that, in
OL,7,Fpractice, it will transfer the cost of
OL,8,Fabout #1.38 billion of currently
OL,9,FGovernment-funded discounts to larger
OL,10,Fratepayers.
OL,12,FAlex Probyn, Ryan's practice leader of
OL,13,Fproperty tax for Europe and Asia-
OL,14,FPacific, said: "The 2026 revaluation
OL,15,Fitself is a redistribution exercise,
OL,16,Fbut when you layer on both inflation
OL,17,Fand the new supplementary multiplier,
OL,18,Fbusinesses are left staring down the
OL,19,Fbarrel of an unavoidable double hit.
